Athrips kostjuki is a moth of the family Gelechiidae. It is found in Russia (Tuva). The habitat consists of semi-deserts.
The wingspan is 15â€“16 mm. The forewings are greyish brown mottled with numerous ochreous scales and with a paired indistinct dark spot near the base and at about one-half, as well as a small spot at two-thirds. The hindwings are grey.